public enum ToistaAani
extends java.lang.Enum<ToistaAani>

This enum encapsulates all the sound effects of a game, so as to separate the sound playing codes from the game codes. 1. Define all your sound effect names and the associated wave file. 2. To play a specific sound, simply invoke ToistaAani.SOUND_NAME.play(). 3. You might optionally invoke the static method ToistaAani.init() to pre-load all the sound files, so that the play is not paused while loading the file for the first time. 4. You can use the static variable ToistaAani.volume to mute the sound.
